Comfort Landscaping & Design is passionate about bringing you professional services at an affordable rate. Here at Comfort Landscaping & Design we believe that your property should be maintained to a standard above the rest. Our main focus is on delivering excellent service to our valued customers the first time around. We hire only the best and brightest to ensure quality service is provided every time.
 
Our technicians will personally evaluate your landscape and work with you to develop a design that meets your unique preferences and suits your property. Do you have a big idea that you want to bring to life? We can help make that a reality so you get a landscape that you will fully enjoy. 
 
One of our motto is ight plant right place\. This means planting plants in their natural environments to ensure proper health and form. We source our plants locally to give you a wide selection of beautiful plants.

houzz.com/professionals/kitchen-and-bath-designers/amy-hart-interior-designer-pfvwus-pf~914450532---Amy Hart began her design career as an Intern with Eastern Michigan University while studying in their top-rated accredited Interior Design program. As a student in 1991 she was charged with heading up the University’s ADA compliance plan which she did successfully. After graduating with a BS in Interior Design and a wealth of practical experience she went on to work in commercial architecture product management operations management and finally found her way into the Kitchen and Bath specialty where she has thrived since 2002.  
After ten years designing for hundreds of people in the Charlottesville market and having been honored with numerous design awards Amy turned her attention to bringing Albemarle Cabinet Co. to life. She is thrilled to foster a team approach to design where the clients have input and a stake in the new design that they are investing in. At the end of the day success is about relationships and communication.
When designing for residential or commercial interiors Amy believes one must “listen” to the structure and strive for a meaningful design that feels right in the space and suits her clients’ personal styles. She doesn’t heed many design “rules” but does believe that a room needs a hero and other characteristics shouldn’t compete for attention. Sometimes the most difficult part of design is to practice restraint.
When not in “design mode” Amy serves as Executive Director for the national non-profit organization Big C New Me bringing much-needed services to cancer survivors and caregivers all over the USA. As a cancer survivor Amy believes in helping others to get back to the business of living and to reach their full potential.

Born in LA raised and educated in the midwest refined in New York City and settled in Asheville North Carolina I am receptive to new ideas and enjoy blending the new with the old. I have been fortunate to have worked for award-winning architecture and interior design firms throughout my career and am conscientious and approachable when it comes to designing for others. I love that with every project I learn something new and I think that even if I continue to design for another 50 years I will be reluctant to use the word “expert” to describe myself. I surround myself with great talent and appreciate the collaborative process with others. I strive to create spaces that offer warmth strength and beauty.

My mission is to offer sincere and authentic design that celebrates our architectural heritage and gives heed to fundamental design principles and established precedent. I believe together we can create homes that are reminiscent of those houses of the past that we treasure so much.

column15: houzz.com/professionals/interior-designers-and-decorators/scott-cokerpadilla-interior-designer-asid-iida-pfvwus-pf~595670574---Scott is a native from Dallas Texas born and raised transported to Minneapolis where he received one of three Bachelors degrees in Interior Design. As a class project in his final year of Design school he was challenged to propose a business plan. Instead of writing it out in black in white he brought it to full fruition and made it a reality. In August 1997 he opened his first Interior Design Studio on Lake Street in Minneapolis and named it “Guilt Trip Interior Design Studio”. Within one year of being open he had paid himself back the original “start up” monies expanded his employees from 3 to 15 sales associates and had 5 NCIDQ Certified Interior Designers working for him selling his merchandise from his store grossing 1.2 million dollars in sales. Within the third year of business he opened his second location in San Diego California off of University Avenue followed by a third location in Mesa Arizona and a fourth location in Dallas Texas inside the Dallas Trade Mart. Now grossing over 5 million dollars a year having over 300 employees having star studded clients on both the East and West coast’s having been published in Architectural Digest Magazine Home and Garden Magazine House Beautiful Magazine Metropolis Midwest Home and Garden being sought out by producers of TLC for his own cable shows and winning countless awards within the Design industry he retired from the business in 2007 by selling his company’s to individual buyers. As a result from the sale he has spent the last 4 years traveling relaxing freelancing to his top priority clients and enjoying life as he wishes. He has been an active Board Member of countless organizations over the past 15 years such as MGRA Kansas City Passages The Climb Minneapolis AIDS Project Center different PRIDE Committees ASID IIDA DIFFA Who’s Who and the list goes on.

houzz.com/professionals/interior-designers-and-decorators/ruxana-s-home-interiors-llc-pfvwus-pf~1166105245---Why have we deleted our portfolio photos?  Quite simply we love what we do.  We combine our passion professionalism enthusiasm and experience to create homes where our clients say they feel happiest.  Our 17 years of repeat and referral clients show our long track record of delivering projects on-time and on-budget.  

We tailor and customize each project to our clients’ needs and budget.  For that reason we have decided to remove our body of work from Houzz and have it exclusively featured on our website: VermontInteriorDesigner.com.  We appreciate the accolades and comments on our work but the inquiries from around the globe asking about a paint color name or the brand of a lighting fixture does not allow us to serve our clients well.    

Houzz has adjusted their business model and now tags and sells products “similar to” items on uploaded photographs and we can take NO RESPONSIBILITY when those items DO NOT WORK in your home.  CAVEAT EMPTOR.  In our firm lighting size proportion shape form scale and texture are carefully calculated and balanced against other elements in each room we design.  In interior design every element selected has ramifications and making a change without taking the whole room into consideration is detrimental to good design.

In the words of Brian Reed: \Everything is designed.  Not everything is designed well.\ 

All the best and have a well-designed day!

Imagine … a refreshing bathroom that invigorates you to tackle a new day; an innovative office that unlocks your creativity; a welcoming family room that enhances your time together; a sensual bedroom that spices up your love life. At Inspired Interiors we use design to transform the way you live love work and function.
 
An award-winning interior architecture firm that specializes in design/ builds/furnish and offers end-to-end services. Comprised of accomplished and creative professionals each with a unique skill set ranging from highly technical knowledge to astute project management the Inspired Interiors team has completed projects ranging from sleek city penthouses and stately suburban estates to high-powered corporate offices and boutique hospitality spaces.

Want to learn more about us? Just Google our name!

houzz.com/professionals/interior-designers-and-decorators/ar-interiors-pfvwus-pf~276906767---I believe my work is important. My job is to make you happy and to improve the quality of your life.

I work for you and it is my privilege to get to know you and to design your home for you. I want you to be my partner in the design process. I listen to what you tell me and your thoughts and needs are my stimulus for my creative process.

I follow the golden rule - and give you advice based on what I would do for me. I will tell you where it is important to spend the money and where and when you can save it.

I consider flexibility an important part of being a designer. Flexibility helps with budget guidelines with material and space constraints with your biases and with your problems and concerns.

I know that this is a business where mistakes happen so I work hard to try and prevent mistakes and to solve them when they do come up. I have learned that solving a problem can often lead to superior design - after all lemonade does come from lemons!

I want you to depend on my honesty - even if the truth hurts! (It’s the good and the bad about me!)

I believe form follows function. That is anything can be made to look beautiful but it must work well in order for it to be characterized as good design.

I like a house to “flow.” That is the colors the style and the feel of the house is consistent throughout. I will work with you to develop a complete palette which will guide us room by room. Different rooms will emphasize and incorporate their own parts of the palette but they will all work together.

I believe good design  takes into consideration all parts of the room - the ceiling the floor the walls the windows the architectural features as well as the furniture and the accessories features as well as the furniture and the accessories.

Established in 1992

We are a 3rd generation family-run business owned and operated by Kim and Greg Berlin. 

Northgate Garage Doors has been located in Marin since 1975 and the Berlin family has been in the overhead door business for over 55 years. 'My grandfather played an important role in the early state of the door industry in the Bay Area starting his own overhead door business in 1948 located in San Francisco. 

\My father moved to Marin in 1975 and started Northgate Overhead doors out of his garage. Some years later he opened 2 more locations. 

I worked with my father side by side for many years and learned all aspects of the door business from sweeping the floors to complex problems solving to building custom doors the time honored way. I am proud and thankful to have been able to learn from my father and grandfather these are things you can't learn from a manual. 

In 1992 I took over the residential overhead door division and my father is still doing industrial doors today.\

For the carriage of furniture packed in special containers there are less stringent requirements. It can be transported as in specially equipped vans and in trucks with flatbed. The customer must mark all units of cargo he must also monitor its loading securing packaging and placement.

Do not leave a lot of empty space between pieces of furniture when transporting them. It can be filled with bags of belongings. You can fill the entire volume by placing lightweight items over large items.

The following tips will help you do this:

- Prepare gear (straps) to carry bulky items.
- Pick up the right tools (hammer pliers screwdriver). You will need them to assemble and disassemble furniture.
- Do not place boxed items on leather furniture.
- Mark with a marker or sign all boxes of parts and number the pieces of a set closet or wall.
- Pack large furniture pieces so that they are easy to move later.

To date moving companies have accumulated a wealth of experience in moving. Try to make the most of it. It is better to learn from others' mistakes.

Do not listen to anyone who tells you that you can do without packing bulky cargo. This operation although it takes time but it saves things in transit. Upon arrival at the new place will only neatly assemble the furniture however and it can be entrusted to a specialist High Stream Moving!

You'll love your new GV Carport. Designed & built to compliment your home a carport is a relatively inexpensive way to protect your car and add value to your property. It will provide new scope for landscaping around your house and for people with north or west-facing walls a carport can also help insulate against long hot summer afternoons.
A verandah is a roofed opened gallery or porch. It is also described as an open pillared gallery generally roofed and built around a central structure.

A carport is a structure used to offer limited protection to vehicles primarily cars from the elements. The structure can either be free standing or attached to a wall. Unlike most structures a carport will not have four walls and is mostly commonly found with only two. Carports offer less protection than garages but allow for more ventilation than garages.

A pergola is a garden feature forming a shaded walk or passageway of pillars that support cross beams and a sturdy open lattice upon which woody vines are trained. It may also be part of a building as protection for an open terrace. The origin of the word is the Late Latin pergola referring to a projecting eave.

column15:
facebook.com/amgelectricltd Residential Wiring

Standard Residential Wiring

The “Canadian Electrical Code” requires a “minimum” when it comes to wiring new homes. Our quotes are based on this “standard.” However, this does not mean that customers cannot add to this minimum requirement.

To avoid future misunderstandings between us and our customers it is helpful to identify as many needs as possible before a quote is given. Clients should give careful thought to all their needs before finalizing a package for quoting.

During our consultation with you, the customer, we will try to address all areas as best we can from our experience to make you aware of some things you may not have thought about. Some examples would be light fixtures vs. pot light or wall sconces, plugs in outside soffits on a switch for a Christmas lighting, kitchen under-cabinet or over-top of cabinet lighting, brighter flood lighting for security outside around the house on motion sensors for extra security, driveway lighting, intercom system, security system, communications or maybe speaker wiring for entertainment.

In some of these cases it is possible to “rough-in” wiring and make final connections in the future to ease financial strain at the end of the building stage. It is our intent to help you “think of everything” before “its too late” to get it installed. Check out our “Future Ready Homes” presentation.

Commercial Wiring

Commercial wiring almost always involves Electrical Engineers and full blueprints. We are bound by these blueprints and design by the Electrical Engineer. In the end, the engineer puts his stamp of approval on our installation called an A9. Our quoting is based on these blue prints and our consultation with the actual customer can be limited in terms of changes or addition. Everything added or changed must be done with the consultation of the engineer. When it comes to commercial installations a set of blue prints is all we need for quoting.

Whatever your project is we are confident that we can bring it to a smooth closing. With 23 likes.

At Andrea Rodman Interiors we create unique elegant and inviting homes custom-designed around our client's lifestyles and tastes.

With our five-step signature design process we walk through the design planning journey with you as a team to create the home of your dreams with positive and collaborative communication.

Our approach is integrative we start with listening to our clients needs lifestyle work lives schedules entertaining requirements and how they would like to live their best lives in their home. We dig into every bit of information to ensure we elevate our client's lives through the design we create together.

Year after year our clients reach out to tell us how much they love their homes. There really is no better feeling for us to hear how much our client's lives have changed and been impacted for the better. Having a positive impact through design drives us to fine-tune our superpowers and inspires us to keep refining and improving our skills for ourselves and our clients.

Designing spaces is what I do. Everyday I feel very grateful to have such a creative outlet and beautiful gathering of clients that choose to open their spaces and families to me and allow me to help design their homes and tell their own personal story. As long as I can remember my focus in life has been on figuring out how things work including people's personality. I have to attribute this to my father who was a Civil Engineer and an Architect extraordinaire. Early memories include visiting his office and being fascinated by his passion for design that inspired me to be a designer.
Born and raised in Mumbai India I have had the opportunity to work with clients across the globe from Miami to London and the Caribbean.
With more than 20 years of experience in Residential Commercial and Hospitality design I have a passion for architecture interior design and creating spaces that are not just functional and stylish but also reflects the personality of my client. I look at every piece of furniture and every object as an individual sculpture.
I have a broad spectrum of experience working on projects ranging from 500 sq. ft. boutique stores to 10000 sq. ft. palatial homes and everything in between.
My work has been featured in leading design publications including West Coast Home and Design Miami Home and Décor and Florida Design to name a few.
As an independent designer my interiors are characterized by my love for detail passion art and design and a style that knows no borders.
Currently based in Vancouver I find inspiration in heritage homes vintage stores and Vancouver's many vibrant neighbourhoods.

column15:
houzz.com/professionals/interior-designers-and-decorators/seasonal-leaf-designs-pfvwus-pf~1451823620---\Seasonal Leaf Interior Design\ is a Design Services & Consultation Full service Interior Design firm offering a range of Design services from one room to the entire home. Reena Venkatesh principal Designer and owner of the company founded Seasonal Leaf Designs in 2006 after having worked with few Design firms in Calcutta-India and WhiteRock-Canada. Her prior experience creating designs for custom Contemporary & Transitional Period furniture Contemporary Tropical theme living areas residential indoor and outdoor landscaping custom horse racing themed restaurant CFIA custom office Pieralisi US office and numerous other residential & commercial designs has given her a unique flair of looking at a space and truly understanding the potential of what can be done. She brings to the table a wealth of experience having worked with a diverse range of residential & commercial clients and other designers. She has the ability to listen to her clients to establish deep trusting relationships with them understand them and to interpret their words into a compelling vision that she turns into an environment that feels right.

Reena says: “We produce interior solutions that are consistent with your vision taste lifestyle and budget. By creating designs that blend your existing space with innovative design features we create a sense of style & comfort resulting in a highly personalized space. We are known for our talent in balancing good design and practical results proper use of space and creating functional designs that speak for themselves and make a difference in your life!”

Reena’s view of Interior Design is straight-forward. Her job is to help her clients create a space that reflects who they are. Whether it is a whole-house renovation or a single-room makeover she believes that a successful interior highlights the expertise of the designer and more importantly speaks to the personality of the client. 

Reena helps her clients capture a \one-of-a-kind look\ that goes beyond the retail identical looks of today’s home furnishings market. Her clients’ ideas photos and family heirlooms often provide inspiration for their rooms. “It’s all about making a house a home” she says “If I can realize my clients’ vision for a space and delight them with the results then that’s a job well done.”

houzz.com/professionals/tile-and-stone/hatton-granite-pfvwus-pf~2115720172---Hatton Granite Company was established in 1904 – making its mark as North Dakota’s oldest monument business. The Company opened its doors in Hatton North Dakota just 15 years after North Dakota gained Statehood. Christian Ness started the business just shortly after settling in Hatton after he and his family emigrated from the Hallingdal area of Norway. In the early years of Hatton Granite the business necessitated personal artistry and design as most of the monuments were created by a hand and chisel. Through the years Hatton Granite saw many changes not only in design but as it passed through the hands of five generations of Christian’s family – Clarence Ness Palmer and Inez (Ness) Wamstad Don and Nicki Wamstad and Blake and Jill Wamstad.

houzz.com/professionals/landscape-contractors/aqua-terra-landscapes-pfvwus-pf~151438547---Aqua-Terra Landscapes began out of owner Thomas Foster's desire to combine many different passions into one career. Tom's training in natural science fine arts and architecture kinesthetic arts horticulture building construction and holistic design brings a varied dimension to Aqua-Terra Landscapes approach to the design/build and the maintenance of Northern California residential living environments.

Owner Thomas Foster grew up playing in creeks and forests of the Eastern United States. After relocating to California in 1990 Tom continues to explore the natural world of our diverse state through backpacking photography and study of natural science. While working in landscape installation and maintenance Tom earned an A.S. in Environmental Horticulture with honors from Butte Community College near Chico CA and has continued self-study in horticulture and landscaping technologies for well over a decade. Tom regards landscapes as an extension of the natural world whose spirit appropriateness and sustainability must be respected.

Tom has an eclectic background which includes work experience and study in textile design photography building construction wildland firefighting teaching martial arts ecology horticulture music and sculpture. Adriana has been a freelance gardener all her life. She grew up in Colombia where she discovered an interest in gardening at a young age. After graduating and obtaining her bachelor degree in Plant and Animal Microbiology she went to Australia to improve her childhood fascination by doing a certificate in Horticulture in Brisbane. 
Arcoiris Design Gardening was born in 2006. Since then Adriana and her husband Juan have grown Arcoiris Design Gardening into a successful Eco-friendly gardening company with over 300 annual flower bed designs/installation and many unique garden builds.  Every garden of their beautiful designs is meticulously and artistic hand made using a wide variety of fabulous plants colors and earth materials. 
Adriana will usually be the first person you meet from the Arcoiris Design Gardening team. Unlike many other garden designers she has a hands-on dynamic style allowing the client to become very much a part of the design process. On paper she will work your garden into a magical place before handing it over to the rest of the team to implement the design. 
Arcoiris Design Gardening has been recognized by multiple awards and green stars by Urban AG Council for their exceptional organic flower beds and amazing gardens. As well as their work has featured in various national magazines and lifestyle publications over the years. 
Most importantly they reduce their environmental foot print by buying from local nurseries and farmers recycling all plastic containers have chemical free gardens use just organic pest control organic fertilizers and organic soil amendments encourage clients to install compost bins teach clients how to grown their veggie-herb garden reusing paper and using only post-consumer recycled paper. Arcoiris Design Gardening recycles more than 98 percent of their waste.

Shannon has over 20 years of experience in interior design on a foundation of a solid education.  She graduated with a Bachelor of Fine Arts Degree in Interior Design from Fashion Institute of Technology (FIT) NYC in 1996 and achieved her MA in Sustainable Interior Environments in May 2013 also from FIT.

As an interior designer color expert and writer Kelly has a unique perspective on color and design. \It's Your Space. Tell Your Story\ is her design mantra. With each and every project she encourages her clients to discover and embrace their own personal style. This has lead to a uniquely diversified - and colorful - portfolio. \I often hear from new clients that they want to work with me because of my use of color. It's the biggest compliment.\r

Kelly earned her BA in Communication from the University of California San Diego and her BFA in Interior Design from the Design Institute of San Diego. She formally studied applied color psychology through the International Association of Color Consultants (IACC-NA) and continues her independent color research on a daily basis. 

With 15 years of design experience Kelly has become a go-to color and design authority for online and print publications including Better Homes and Gardens and Woman's Day. Inspired by her mother’s love of style and art and father’s engineering and business savvy Susan’s passion for design is fueled by her love of architecture art materials modern culture history fashion entertaining and hospitality.

As a teenager Susan remembers looking around a room and connecting the dots.  Tracing a mental line from the tops of the door casing to the mirror to the window and thinking how she would change it. Following her passion she received a degree in Interior Design in 1976 and hasn’t stopped learning since. In 1987 she opened her own award winning design firm. She enjoys and is passionate about creating beautiful functional accessible and healthy interiors that enlighten the occupant’s daily lives.  

Susan is a Florida licensed Registered Interior Designer a professional member of ASID (American Society of Interior Designers) of which she is past president of the Florida South Chapter.  She has been on the ASID National Aging in Place Council.  She is certified by NCIDQ (National Council of Interior Design Qualification) a Certified Aging in Place Specialist (CAPS) a LEED AP (Leadership in Energy Efficient Design Accredited Professional) and a certified Green Leader through the Sustainable Furnishings Council. She is an Allied Member of AIA a member of the Treasure Coast Chapter of USGBC a member of NKBA the Sustainable Furnishings Council and the Luxury Marketing Council.

Barbara has loved design and décor for as long as she can remember.  She spent the first half of her life in Richmond Virginia exposed to traditional southern architecture.  Moving her way through the northeastern half of the country she’s developed a style that is a combination of traditional and classic with just a hint of modern.  She also knows that décor has to be practical.  

With two kids a husband and dog she’s realistic about creating spaces that are true to your daily life.  Good design is a conversation between beauty comfort and lifestyle.

Having close relationships with expert builders architects and crafters have made her well equipped to translate your ideas into realistic and concrete plans.  The design starts with you.  She has a client-focused approach to design making you her top priority.  Probing into your own style she guides you through the process of creating a thoughtful personal space that fit both your taste and lifestyle. Her attention and interest in the details of a project mean you don’t have to be bothered. 
 
Getting to know her clients personally is one of the most satisfying parts of her work.  The process begins and ends with you in mind.  There is nothing more transformative than living in surroundings that reflect who you are and the things you find beautiful.
